text: Cesvaine Parish () is an administrative unit of Cesvaine Municipality, Latvia. It was created in 2010 from the countryside territory of Cesvaine town. At the beginning of 2014, the population of the parish was 1356. == Towns, villages and settlements of Cesvaine parish == * Graši * Kārkli * Kārzdaba * Kraukļi == References == Category:Parishes of Latvia Category:Cesvaine Municipality
